<item>
            <title>[MSHADE-363] Breaking change to ResourceTransformer&apos;s API</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-363</link>
                <project id="12317921" key="MSHADE">Maven Shade Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A Spring Boot user has &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/21128&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;made us aware&lt;/a&gt; of a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/0d7bfb53a5fd83eede7edfd5552db5fa561d6286#diff-f09094e2212bb4d1173a4e183635b958&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;breaking change to the API of ResourceTransformer&lt;/a&gt; in 3.2.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally, we don&apos;t want to require a specific version of the Shade plugin. While I think we may be able to support the new and old both variants of the method, it would be preferable if future 3.2.x releases are backwards compatible with 3.2.2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13301091">MSHADE-363</key>
            <summary>Breaking change to ResourceTransformer&apos;s API</summary>
