                <updated>Sat, 14 Jun 2025 18:11:48 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Thu, 14 May 2020 21:40:55 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>3.2.3</version>
                                    <fixVersion>3.2.4</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17092765" author="hboutemy" created="Sun, 26 Apr 2020 16:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sorry, I did not imagine that this API was used: I now see you use it to write new ResourceTransformers...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it&apos;s too late to change the past, I did the mistake: can I do something to improve the situation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17092808" author="rfscholte" created="Sun, 26 Apr 2020 18:00:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it possible to push the plugin to Java 8 and add a default method? (That&apos;s the original intention of default methods)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17097361" author="awilkinson" created="Fri, 1 May 2020 13:15:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If reverting the change is not an option, requiring Java 8 and adding a default method is the only thing that I can think of.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17097466" author="hboutemy" created="Fri, 1 May 2020 15:53:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, I&apos;ll revert to release 3.2.4&lt;br/&gt;
and I&apos;ll use this Java 8 approach for 3.3.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17098398" author="hudson" created="Sun, 3 May 2020 12:09:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build succeeded in Jenkins: Maven TLP &#187; maven-shade-plugin &#187; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-363&quot; title=&quot;Breaking change to ResourceTransformer&amp;#39;s API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSHADE-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSHADE-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; #3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/MSHADE-363/3/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/MSHADE-363/3/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17098466" author="hudson" created="Sun, 3 May 2020 15:08:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build succeeded in Jenkins: Maven TLP &#187; maven-shade-plugin &#187; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-363&quot; title=&quot;Breaking change to ResourceTransformer&amp;#39;s API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSHADE-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSHADE-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; #4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/MSHADE-363/4/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/MSHADE-363/4/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17098478" author="hboutemy" created="Sun, 3 May 2020 15:47:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;everything is available in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-363&quot; title=&quot;Breaking change to ResourceTransformer&amp;#39;s API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSHADE-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSHADE-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; branch:&lt;br/&gt;
1. I added an IT to show the failure and check the fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/09274366f74b4f0b61ba4ad91d70ac9c29d05c50&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/09274366f74b4f0b61ba4ad91d70ac9c29d05c50&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2. I changed ResourceTransformer back and added ReproducibleResourceTransformer for the new reproducible behaviour in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/3d0af7704b227d6c9007550c246b9063f73b6a0c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/3d0af7704b227d6c9007550c246b9063f73b6a0c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
3. I added an IT to check how implementation of this new ReproducibleResourceTransformer can be run in old shade plugin by simply adding the interface (source copy or shade...) in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/124225566880d8bfa2b4b30ee86dab45b66b39b6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/124225566880d8bfa2b4b30ee86dab45b66b39b6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if no objection, I&apos;ll merge to master and do 3.2.4 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17098479" author="hboutemy" created="Sun, 3 May 2020 15:53:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;notice that since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-322&quot; title=&quot;Provide a transformer for properties files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSHADE-322&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSHADE-322&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in maven-shade-plugin 3.2.2, there are some properties merger in &lt;a href=&quot;https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/apidocs/org/apache/maven/plugins/shade/resource/properties/package-frame.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/apidocs/org/apache/maven/plugins/shade/resource/properties/package-frame.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
perhaps this could be useful instead of Spring custom transformer&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17099048" author="awilkinson" created="Mon, 4 May 2020 15:34:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the pointer, Herve. I&apos;d missed the addition of &lt;tt&gt;PropertiesTransformer&lt;/tt&gt;. I&apos;ve opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/21307&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/21307&lt;/a&gt;&#160;so that we can make use of it in Spring Boot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17107233" author="hudson" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 11:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build failed in Jenkins: Maven TLP &#187; maven-shade-plugin &#187; master #92&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/master/92/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-shade-plugin/job/master/92/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17107706" author="hboutemy" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 21:40:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;merged to master:&lt;br/&gt;
1. IT to show the failure and check the fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/51bbf72e195e34229a1d3ebba2f9608255068a9d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/51bbf72e195e34229a1d3ebba2f9608255068a9d&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2. changed ResourceTransformer back and added ReproducibleResourceTransformer for the new reproducible behaviour in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/229f4d79836b20a17dd8291e3734fae8c982b811&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/229f4d79836b20a17dd8291e3734fae8c982b811&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
3. added an IT to check how implementation of this new ReproducibleResourceTransformer can be run in old shade plugin by simply adding the interface (source copy or shade...) in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/4f83ae693f5c9f8022fc2b75c83b2bd632a1b6c8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/commit/4f83ae693f5c9f8022fc2b75c83b2bd632a1b6c8&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17108977" author="awilkinson" created="Sat, 16 May 2020 10:16:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Following up on the suggestion to use &lt;tt&gt;PropertiesTransformer&lt;/tt&gt;, unfortunately it does not meet our needs. Boot&#8217;s transformer combines values for the same key by comma separating them, i.e we merge the values rather than overriding.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17976114" author="JIRAUSER302100" created="Sat, 14 Jun 2025 18:11:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-shade-plugin/issues/554&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-shade-plugin#554&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
